value.value: A collagen alpha chain that is a translation product of the human COL1A1 or COL1A2 genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof.

label.value: apoptosis regulator BAX isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: An apoptosis regulator BAX isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.
An apoptosis regulator BAX isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs at a Ser residue upon AKT activation. Example: UniProtKB:Q07813-1, Ser-184, MOD:00046.

label.value: Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated 6

value.value: A Bcl2-associated agonist of cell death isoform 1 phosphorylated form in which the phosphorylation occurs by the action of cdc-2. Example: UniProtKB:Q61337-1, Ser-128/Ser-136, MOD:00046.

A protein that is cyclin-dependent kinase. The activated form phosphorylates target substrates on Ser or Thr residues followed by a proline. The core domain architecture consists of a copy of the Protein kinase domain (Pfam:PF00069).
A CDK2-related kinase that is a translation product of the human CDK1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that has a core domain composition consisting of a Receptor L domain (Pfam:PF01030) followed by a Furin-like cysteine rich region (Pfam:PF00757) and a second copy of the Receptor L domain (Pfam:PF01030), two to four copies of the Fibronectin type 3 domain (Pfam:PF00041) and a copy of the Protein tyrosine kinase (Pfam:PF07714) domain at the C-terminus.
An insulin receptor-related receptor that is a translation product of the human IGF1R gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

An insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:P08069-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor isoform 1 cleaved 1

value.value: An insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been subsequently processed to yield the N-terminal mature chain.

label.value: insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor isoform 1 cleaved 2

value.value: An insulin-like growth factor 1 receptor isoform 1, signal peptide removed form that has been subsequently processed to yield the C-terminal mature chain.
A protein that is a translation product of the human PPP3CA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

label.value: interferon regulatory factor 7 isoform 1 phosphorylated form

value.value: An interferon regulatory factor 7 isoform 1 that includes at least one phosphorylated residue.

An interferon regulatory factor 7 isoform 1 phosphorylated form that has been activated by phosphorylation on the Ser residues located in the C-terminal region. Phosphorylation stimulates the C-terminal autoinhibitory domain to attain a highly extended conformation triggering dimerization through extensive contacts to a second subunit. Example: UniProtKB:Q92985-1, Ser-477/Ser-479, MOD:00046.

label.value: TRAF-interacting protein with FHA domain-containing protein B

A protein that is a stand alone version of the Ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme (Pfam:PF00179) domain. This class is called typical because it contains an essential Cys residue and hence the catalytic activity required to form a thiol-ester with ubiquitin in the second step of ubiquitination.
A typical ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme E2 that is a translation product of the human UBE2N gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that contains a central Ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme (Pfam:PF00179) domain that has significant similarity to true ubiquitin-conjugating enzymes (Ubcs). However, unlike typical Ubcs, this class lacks the essential Cys residue and hence the catalytic activity required to form a thiol-ester with ubiquitin in the second step of ubiquitination.
A ubiquitin-conjugating enzyme variant that is a translation product of the human UBE2V1 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A protein that is a translation product of the human NFKBIA, NFKBIB, or NFKBIE genes, 1:1 orthologs thereof, or a semi-ortholog thereof. It contains multiple copies of the Ankyrin repeats (Pfam:PF00023 or Pfam:PF12796).
An NF-kappa-B inhibitor that is a translation product of the human NFKBIA gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An NF-kappa-B inhibitor that is a translation product of the human NFKBIB gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
An NF-kappa-B inhibitor that is a translation product of the human NFKBIE gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
A protein that is a translation product of the human LY96 gene or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.

A lymphocyte antigen 96 that is a translation product of some mRNA whose exon structure and start site selection renders it capable of giving rise to a protein with the amino acid sequence represented by UniProtKB:Q9Y6Y9-1 or a 1:1 ortholog thereof.
